## COMBINATION SWITCH REMOVAL/INSTALLATION  


1. Disconnect the negative battery cable.  
2. Remove the driver-side air bag module. (Refer to 08-10 DRIVER-SIDE AIR BAG MODULE REMOVAL/INSTALLATION.)  
3. Remove the steering wheel. (Refer to 06-12 STEERING WHEEL AND COLUMN REMOVAL/INSTALLATION.)  
4. Remove the column cover.  
5. Remove the clock spring. (Refer to 08-10 CLOCK SPRING REMOVAL/INSTALLATION.)  
6. Remove in the order indicated in the table.  
7. Install in the reverse order of removal.  


